00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:40.869
Medical illustrator Emily Evans created a
set of Histology plates with the help of her

00:01:40.869 --> 00:01:45.960
colleagues in the medical and art fields.
She was provided with prepared slides of various

00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:51.350
stained and scanned human tissues and worked
with a ceramic artist to make the plates.

00:01:51.350 --> 00:01:55.219
They are 20 cm bone china cake plates and
come in 8 different human tissue designs,

00:01:55.219 --> 00:01:57.380
Thyroid, Bowel, Liver, Bone, Pancreas, Oesophagus,
Kidney and Testicle.&nbsp;

00:01:57.380 --> 00:02:03.689
99 Steps of progress is a series of illustrations
that parody the famous march of progress created

00:02:03.689 --> 00:02:09.420
by Paris artist collective, Maentis. A new
illustration is unveiled each day for 99 days

00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:13.280
and each design is available for purchase
in a variety of formats including prints,

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:16.420
posters, tshits &amp; hoodies. Check out the website
for the latest edition.

